        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 12:15AM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 1214 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 7 miles southeast of Burlington to Bronson.
Movement was east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Coldwater, Hillsdale, Bronson, Jonesville, Quincy, Litchfield,
Reading, Long Lake, Jerome, Somerset, Cambria, Girard, Pittsford,
Kinderhook, Moscow, Batavia, California, Ransom, Gilead, and North
Adams.

This includes Interstate 69 in Michigan between mile markers 1 and
21.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 300 AM EDT for southwestern
Michigan.</instruction>
